@startuml RoarFitnessERP_Visitor_Register_Login_VIP_Booking
title Visitor Journey — Public Website → Register → Login → VIP Session Booking

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor Visitor
participant "Public Website\n(frontend :5200)" as PublicFE
participant "Register / Payment\n(frontend)" as AuthFE
participant "Member Portal\n(frontend)" as MemberFE
participant "RoarFitnessERP API\n(backend :5188)" as API
database "SQL Server" as DB

== 1. Browse public website ==
Visitor -> PublicFE : Open home, plans, classes pages
PublicFE -> API : GET /api/public/packages
API -> DB : Load membership packages
API --> PublicFE : Packages for pricing / join

PublicFE -> API : GET /api/public/general-classes
API --> PublicFE : Weekly general class schedule

PublicFE -> API : GET /api/public/vip-sessions?date={YYYY-MM-DD}
API -> DB : Accepted VIP sessions for date
API --> PublicFE : VIP session cards (read-only)
PublicFE --> Visitor : Show schedule;\nVIP cards display\n"VIP Members Only"

Visitor -> PublicFE : Click Join / Get Membership
PublicFE --> AuthFE : Navigate to /join → /register?plan={id}

== 2. Register & activate membership ==
Visitor -> AuthFE : Complete registration form
AuthFE -> API : POST /api/membership/register\n{ email, password, profile, packageId }
API -> DB : Create User + Member (pending payment)
API --> AuthFE : { memberId, identificationNumber, packageId }

AuthFE -> API : POST /api/payment-gateway/membership/init\n?memberId=&packageId=
API -> DB : Create Payment (Pending, Membership)
API --> AuthFE : { paymentReference, checkoutUrl }

AuthFE -> AuthFE : Save pending registration (sessionStorage)
Visitor -> AuthFE : Confirm payment on /payment (mock card)
AuthFE -> API : POST /api/payment-gateway/membership/confirm\n?packageId=\n{ paymentReference, gatewayTransactionId }
API -> DB : Mark payment Completed;\nactivate Membership
API --> AuthFE : { message: "Membership activated." }
AuthFE --> Visitor : Payment success → go to login

== 3. Log in to member account ==
Visitor -> AuthFE : Submit login credentials
AuthFE -> API : POST /api/authentication/login\n{ email, password }
API -> DB : Validate user, roles, membership status
API --> AuthFE : { token, userId, email, fullName, roles: ["Member"] }
AuthFE -> AuthFE : Store JWT; signIn(member)
AuthFE --> MemberFE : Redirect to Member Portal (/dashboard)

== 4. Book a VIP session ==
Visitor -> MemberFE : Open VIP Sessions
MemberFE -> API : GET /api/special-sessions/member/available\nAuthorization: Bearer {token}
API -> DB : Accepted sessions with spots;\nexclude already enrolled
API --> MemberFE : Available VIP sessions list

Visitor -> MemberFE : Click Enroll on a session
MemberFE -> API : POST /api/payment-gateway/session/init\n?sessionId={id}
API -> DB : Validate session;\ncreate Payment (Pending, Session)
API --> MemberFE : { paymentReference }

MemberFE -> MemberFE : Save pending session payment
Visitor -> MemberFE : Confirm session fee on /payment
MemberFE -> API : POST /api/payment-gateway/session/confirm\n?sessionId=\n{ paymentReference, gatewayTransactionId }
API -> DB : Complete payment;\nINSERT SpecialSessionEnrollment
API --> MemberFE : Enrollment confirmed

MemberFE -> API : GET /api/special-sessions/member/mine
API --> MemberFE : Enrolled VIP sessions
MemberFE --> Visitor : Show booking under "My Sessions"

note over Visitor, DB
  **Systems in scope:** frontend (React SPA) + backend (ASP.NET API).
  Fingerprint simulator is not part of this flow.
  Membership payment must succeed before login;
  VIP enrollment requires an active member account.
end note

@enduml
